  "chapter": {
    "number": 1,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Paulâ€™s Greeting to Timothy"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Paul, an apostle of Christ Jesus by the will of God, according to the promise of life in Christ Jesus,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "To Timothy, my beloved child:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          "Grace, mercy, and peace from God the Father and Christ Jesus our Lord."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Faithfulness under Persecution"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "I thank God, whom I serve with a clear conscience as did my forefathers, as I constantly remember you night and day in my prayers."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "Recalling your tears, I long to see you so that I may be filled with joy."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "I am reminded of your sincere faith, which first dwelt in your grandmother Lois and your mother Eunice, and I am convinced is in you as well."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "For this reason I remind you to fan into flame the gift of God, which is in you through the laying on of my hands."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          "For God has not given us a spirit of fear,",
          {
            "noteId": 1122
          },
          "but of power, love, and self-control."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          "So do not be ashamed of the testimony of our Lord, or of me, His prisoner. Instead, join me in suffering for the gospel by the power of God."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          "He has saved us and called us to a holy calling, not because of our works, but by His own purpose and by the grace He granted us in Christ Jesus before time began.",
          {
            "noteId": 1123
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          "And now He has revealed this grace through the appearing of our Savior, Christ Jesus, who has abolished death and illuminated the way to life and immortality through the gospel,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "to which I was appointed as a preacher, an apostle, and a teacher."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          "For this reason, even though I suffer as I do, I am not ashamed; for I know whom I have believed, and I am convinced that He is able to guard what I have entrusted to Him",
          {
            "noteId": 1124
          },
          "for that day."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Holding to Sound Teaching"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          "Hold on to the pattern of sound teaching",
          {
            "noteId": 1125
          },
          "you have heard from me, with the faith and love that are in Christ Jesus."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          "Guard the treasure entrusted to you,",
          {
            "noteId": 1126
          },
          "with the help of the Holy Spirit who dwells in us."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          "You know that everyone in the Province of Asia",
          {
            "noteId": 1127
          },
          "has deserted me, including Phygelus and Hermogenes."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          "May the Lord grant mercy to the household of Onesiphorus, because he has often refreshed me and was unashamed of my chains."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          "Indeed, when he arrived in Rome, he searched diligently until he found me."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          "May the Lord grant Onesiphorus His mercy on that day. You know very well how much he ministered to me in Ephesus."
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 1122,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or timidity or cowardice",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 7
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 1123,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Literally before times eternal",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 9
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 1124,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or what He has entrusted to me",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 12
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 1125,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Literally sound words",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 13
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 1126,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or the good deposit entrusted to you",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 14
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 1127,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Literally in Asia; Asia was a Roman province in what is now western Turkey.",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 1,
          "verse": 15
        }
      }
    ]
  },
